  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subjects who require the implantation of an Implantable Cardioverter Defibrillator

          -  Subjects who have heart failure that severely limits daily activities (NYHA Class III)
             or Subjects who have severe heart failure and should always be resting (NYHA Class IV)

          -  Subjects with reduced heart pumping function (left ventricular ejection fraction ≤
             35%)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Subjects who have constant atrial fibrillation (top chambers of the heart beat too
             fast continuously)

          -  Subjects who are post-heart transplant
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
